result.execSummary:
The defendant John J. Rosciszewski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Reminder Notice indicating amount due mailed to defendant.

(Case called at 9:41 AM- by Zoom) Defendant John J. Rosciszewski appeared by video, in custody from Rusk County Jail.  Attorney Ryan Glenn Kohler in court.  Prosecuting attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defense indicates there is an agreement. Court recites the joint sentence recommendation. Defendant waives his right to personal appearance- Court accepts waiver of personal appearance.  
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1- Resisting an Officer. Court accepts plea and finds the Defendant guilty. Remaining charges are dismissed and read in. 
Court orders Defendant to serve 10 days jail with 2 days credit (may be served by 80 hours of Community Service- Defendant chooses Community Service), Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge, Court costs.
